      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      LbServiceUsage.Builder LbServiceUsage.Builder.setCurrentPoolCount(Long currentPoolCount)

      LbServiceUsage.Builder LbServiceUsage.Builder.setCurrentPoolMemberCount(Long currentPoolMemberCount)
      The current number of pool members which has been configured in the given load balancer service.
      LbServiceUsage.Builder LbServiceUsage.Builder.setCurrentVirtualServerCount(Long currentVirtualServerCount)
      The current number of virtual servers which has been configured in the given load balancer service.
      LbServiceUsage.Builder LbServiceUsage.Builder.setPoolCapacity(Long poolCapacity)
      Pool capacity means maximum number of pools which could be configured in the given load balancer service.
      LbServiceUsage.Builder LbServiceUsage.Builder.setPoolMemberCapacity(Long poolMemberCapacity)
      Pool member capacity means maximum number of pool members which could be configured in the given load balancer service.
      LbServiceUsage.Builder LbServiceUsage.Builder.setServiceId(String serviceId)
      UUID of load balancer service This property may be present in responses from the server, but if it is present in a request to server it will be ignored.
      LbServiceUsage.Builder LbServiceUsage.Builder.setServiceSize(String serviceSize)
      Possible values are: LbServiceUsage.SERVICE_SIZE_SMALL, LbServiceUsage.SERVICE_SIZE_MEDIUM, LbServiceUsage.SERVICE_SIZE_LARGE, LbServiceUsage.SERVICE_SIZE_DLB, The size of load balancer service This property may be present in responses from the server, but if it is present in a request to server it will be ignored.
      LbServiceUsage.Builder LbServiceUsage.Builder.setSeverity(String severity)
      Possible values are: LbServiceUsage.SEVERITY_GREEN, LbServiceUsage.SEVERITY_ORANGE, LbServiceUsage.SEVERITY_RED, The severity calculation is based on the largest usage percentage from virtual servers, pools and pool members for one load balancer service.
      LbServiceUsage.Builder LbServiceUsage.Builder.setUsagePercentage(Double usagePercentage)
      The usage percentage is the largest usage percentage from virtual servers, pools and pool members for the load balancer service.
      LbServiceUsage.Builder LbServiceUsage.Builder.setVirtualServerCapacity(Long virtualServerCapacity)
      Virtual server capacity means maximum number of virtual servers which could be configured in the given load balancer service.
